DIGEST
SB 395 Original 2026 Regular Session Miguez
Proposed law provides that when a property is owned the country of China, the Chinese
Communist Party, a corporation incorporated in the country of China, or a person who is a
citizen of the country of China, the state will expropriate the property, which will be deemed
to be an exercise of its state governmental powers.
Proposed law provides that the taking will be considered as necessary for a public purpose
pursuant to the La. Constitution.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 19:2.3)
